# hexa-lang /.doc — docs organization SSOT (raw-format DSL)
# Spec: docs/formats/doc.md (cross-repo) — hive owns the spec, hexa-lang consumes
# Lint: ./build/hexa_stage0 tool/doc_lint.hexa (or hive's tool/doc_lint.hexa)

doc 0 live "docs/ folder layout — hexa-lang dual-dir reconciliation"
  slug docs-folder-layout
  enforce tool/doc_lint.hexa
  scope docs/**
  decl docs/README.md docs/design/ docs/formats/
  why docs/ has 16 .md (2026-04 design); doc/ has 12 .md (older reference). Dual-dir is technical debt — declare both, then consolidate doc/ → docs/.

doc 1 live "doc/ legacy reference dir (consolidation deferred)"
  slug docs-legacy-doc-dir
  status deferred
  scope doc/**
  defer-until phase-3 consolidation (ROI: low — moving 12 stable .md)
  why pre-existing reference docs; preserve in place until cross-link audit confirms zero external refs.

doc 2 live "kebab-case + no version/temp suffixes + frontmatter required"
  slug docs-file-conventions
  enforce tool/doc_lint.hexa
  scope docs/**/*.md
  bans _v\d+ _mk\d+ _old _new _bak _tmp leading-YYYY-MM-DD-
  why mirror hive .doc 1 + .doc 2 conventions for cross-repo doc grep-ability.
